						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 2) set up near the west wall of the Sōmanātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Bukka I, 1379-80 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1[3]01, Siddhārthi,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1379-80 A.D.</hi> It registers a gift of land for the worship and offerings and for feeding two Brāhmaṇas in the temple of Sōmanāthadēva. The details of date etc., are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
